  "justification": "This function implements the three-way merge algorithm for Settings Sync. It takes three ICompareResult objects (localToRemote, baseToLocal, baseToRemote), each containing added/removed/updated sets. It returns an object with four Sets: added, removed, updated, and conflicts. The procedure matches exactly: (1) iterates baseToLocal.removed - if baseToRemote.updated has the key, marks as conflict; (2) iterates baseToRemote.removed - if baseToLocal.updated has the key, marks as conflict, otherwise accepts removal; (3) iterates baseToLocal.added - if also in baseToRemote.added with different value (localToRemote.updated), marks as conflict; (4) iterates baseToRemote.added - if also in baseToLocal.added with different value, marks as conflict, otherwise accepts addition; (5) iterates baseToLocal.updated - if also in baseToRemote.updated with different value, marks as conflict; (6) iterates baseToRemote.updated - if also in baseToLocal.updated with different value, marks as conflict, otherwise accepts update. Already-conflicted keys are skipped via conflicts.has(key) guards throughout."
}

